<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Resume Screener</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/navbar.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/resume.css">
</head>
<body>
  {{> jobsNavbar}}
  <div class="resume-screener-wrapper">

    <section class="hero">
      <h1>📄 Resume Screener</h1>
      <p>Want to know if your resume is ATS-friendly? Upload your resume and get an instant score!</p>
      <form action="/resume/screener" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data" class="hero-form">
        <input type="file" name="resume" accept=".pdf" required>
        <button type="submit">🎯 Get My ATS Score</button>
      </form>
    </section>

    <section class="why-screening">
      <h2>🔍 Why Resume Screening Matters</h2>
      <p>
        Over 95% of top companies use Applicant Tracking Systems (ATS) to filter resumes. If your resume lacks the right format, keywords, or structure — it might be rejected before a human sees it.
        Our tool simulates real ATS behavior and provides detailed feedback so you can:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>✅ Know your ATS score out of 100</li>
        <li>📌 Identify missing job-specific keywords</li>
        <li>📄 Improve formatting, project, and experience sections</li>
        <li>🚀 Increase your chances of getting shortlisted</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    

    <section class="extra-note">
      <p><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Targeting a software developer role? Make sure your resume includes technologies like <em>JavaScript, React, Node.js, MongoDB</em>, and <em>projects</em> that demonstrate real-world application!</p>
    </section>

  </div>

</body>
</html>
